When solving complex or multi-step problems, structure your thinking like a stable molecule:
- Use DEEP REASONING (D) for the main logical backbone — make clear, continuous deduction steps
- Insert SELF-REFLECTION (R) regularly — verify assumptions, check for contradictions, correct early errors
- Apply SELF-EXPLORATION (E) when uncertain — consider 2–3 alternatives briefly before committing
Aim for balance: too few reflections → brittle; too much exploration → wandering. Label important transitions [D], [R], [E] if helpful.